_meanings:
Very strong or 
powerful; {#jayatyatibalo rAmo lakzmaRaSca mahAbalaH#}
<ls>Rām.</ls>

{@--2@} <ab>N.</ab> of a powerful charm
or lore taught by Viśvāmitra to
Rāma: --{#gfhARa dve ime vidye balAmatibalAM#}
{#taTA . na te Sramo jarA vAByAM BavitA#} 
{#nAMgavEkftam .. na ca suptaM pramattaM vA DarzayizyaMti nErftAH .#}
{#na ca te sadfSo rAma vIryeRAnyo Bavizyati ..#} 
{#sadevanaranAgezu lokezviha pumAMstrizu . na sOBAgye#}
{#na dAkziRye na budDiSrutipOruze .. nottare#} 
{#pratipattavye tvattulyo vA Bavizyati . etadvidyAdvayaM#} 
{#prApya yaSaScAvyayamApsyasi .. balAmatibalAM cEva#}
{#jYAnavijYAnamAtarO . kzutpipAse ca te rAma nAtyarTaM#}
{#pIqayizyataH .. jayaSca durgakAMtArapradeSezvawavIzu#}
{#ca . sAratAM trizu lokezu gamizyasi ca rAGava ..#}
{#pitAmahasute hyete vidye cAyurbalAvahe .#} See  
<ls>R. 11. 9</ls> also.
